Chilled Avocado Soup
  -Jose Enrique

¼ c + 3 tbsp olive oil, divided
4 garlic cloves, peeled and crushed
1 white onion, roughly chopped
3 c water
¼ c cilantro leaves + more for garnish
2 tbsp lime juice
2 ripe avocados, peeled and pitted
Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper, to taste
1 c small-diced watermelon
1 tbsp lemon juice
Crumbled queso fresco, for garnish

In a large skillet, heat 1 tbsp of oilive oil over medium heat. Add the garlic and onion, and sweat until translucent, 10 min. Add the water and transfer to a blender to cool completely. Add the cilantro, lime juice and avocados to the blender. With the motor running, slowly pour in ¼ c of the olive oil. Season with salt and pepper, then chill in the refrigerator. In a small bowl, toss the watermelon with the remaining 2 tbsp of olive oil and lemon juice, then season with salt and pepper. Divide the soup between small shooter glasses and garnish each with watermelon, queso fresco and cilantro, then serve.
